From b613ec044e6b068a3968ea04cca69a9029c5a456 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mario Lohajner <mario_lohajner@rocketmail.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 00:11:06 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ext4: rralloc - add round-robin allocation policy and
 optimize stream mode

V3 is a progressive upgrade from V2:
- maintains standard rralloc features
- per-CPU starting points to minimize lock contention.
- per-inode atomic cursors
- strict allocator isolation
- rralloc remains an optional mount flag.
NEW:
- Reworked standard allocator stream mode to use atomic per-inode cursors
  instead of the legacy hash array of global goals to improve tail latency.
- Built directly for and verified against the recent Fedora v7.1.3 kernel tree.

Modified structures:
- fs/ext4/ext4.h    : Declare rralloc policy, per-CPU cursors, and allocator vector.
- fs/ext4/ialloc.c  : Initialize (zero out) the per-inode cursor.
- fs/ext4/mballoc.h : Expose allocator functions for tracking inside super.c.
- fs/ext4/super.c   : Parse rralloc mount option, initialize per-CPU cursors.
- fs/ext4/mballoc.c : Implement rotating allocator and vectored allocation path.

Signed-off-by: Mario Lohajner <mario_lohajner@rocketmail.com>
---
